06/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Britain on Friday (3 September) ratified Croatia's association agreement with the EU, opening the way for the start of accession talks with Zagreb. 
London had refused to endorse the deal because of Croatia's insufficient co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal.
In other news, Croatia on Saturday participated in its first EU ministerial meeting. 
Foreign Minister Miomir Zuzul was on hand for an informal meeting of counterparts from 25 member countries in Valkenburg, the Netherlands. 
(HINA, HRT - 04/09/04; AFP - 03/09/04)
